ing here in most auspicious form, thereafter grant us the blessings that ar=
e free from sin.

=C2=A0the invocation is being made to pitru devataas to c=
ome and accept the offerings prepared by us and then favour us by providing=
 health and blessings free from sin - seems to be a bribe being made to pit=
ru devataas, certainly not. the request is to bestow sinless peace and tran=
quility upon us, the word rapaH is a synonymn for sin and arapaH is opposit=
e of that i.e. sinless. the request is to grant peace and tranquility that =
is sinless upon us (naH shaM yoH arapaH dadhaata). One will attain sinless =
peace when there is "in-action in action" and that is sacrifice/yaGYa/pitru=
 kaarya, one can attain peace (temporary) by "no-action" but that is sinful=
, and sacrifices such as yaGYa/pitru kaarya are ones dharma (actually a RRi=
Na), hence the requisition is for a dharmic cause - to help us (uuti) by pr=
oviding sinless peace (arapaH - shaM), arapaH also means free from disease =
(i.e health) so the requisition can also be translated as - to help us by p=
roviding
 auspicious blessing and health (connected to earlier rik RV10.015=
